    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot discs</strong> and <strong>sliced leek</strong> with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 120ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[160ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 7-8 min or until the carrot is tender with a slight bite – this is your <strong>buttery veg</strong></p>",
